'''Sianoa Smit-McPhee''' (born 21 February 1992) is an Australian actress. She is best known for her two years in Australian soap ''[[Neighbours]]'' as [[Bree Timmins|Breanna Timmins]].<ref>[http://www.perfectblend.net/comment/ltn-bree.htm Neighbours: The Perfect Blend | Love Thy Neighbour: Bree Timmins]. The Perfect Blend. Retrieved on 15 January 2011.</ref> Sianoa's next role was in the children's television series ''[[As the Bell Rings]]'', which used to air on the [[Disney Channel]].
In 2007, Sianoa appeared as Desma, the lead character in the short fantasy film, Hugo. Since 2009, Sianoa has starred in the American HBO series ''[[Hung (TV series)|Hung]]'' as Darby Drecker.
==Family== Sianoa was born in [[Adelaide]], South Australia. She showed an interest in performing at the age of two, inspired by her actor father, Andy McPhee.{{Citation needed|date=April 2011}} She was singing, dancing, acting and modeling by the age of three.{{Citation needed|date=April 2011}} When Sianoa was seven she moved to Melbourne with her parents and her younger brother, [[Kodi Smit-McPhee]], who is also an actor.<ref>[http://www.tv.com/sianoa-smit-mcphee/person/364716/summary.html Sianoa Smit-McPhee on]. Tv.com (19 January 2006). Retrieved on 15 January 2011.</ref> Sianoa has had many roles in film, theatre, commercials and television, including the part of Charlie in ''[[Blue Heelers]]''. Sianoa's brother [[Kodi Smit-McPhee]] starred in the 2007 movie ''[[Romulus, My Father (film)|Romulus, My Father]]'', acting beside [[Eric Bana]].
